metadata.name: OPENING
metadata.description:
In the 60s, Leo Castelli made posters for all his artists shows. The artists would sign a stack, and Castelli would sell them for $10-$50 each to help cover office expenses. 

Today, those posters have a tradable value all their own. 

As a token of my gratitude, you now have my first 'poster' following my acceptance to @SuperRare

I wanted to commemorate the moment, and share it with some of you who helped me get here today! 

Thank you so much. 

C
